President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Kansas and ordered federal aid to support recovery efforts following severe storms, flooding, straight-line winds, and tornadoes that occurred between April 25 and May 16, 2009. Federal funding will be provided to state and local governments, as well as certain nonprofit organizations, for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. The affected counties include Anderson, Barber, Bourbon, Butler, Chase, Cherokee, Coffey, Cowley, Crawford, Elk, Finney, Greenwood, Harper, Harvey, Kingman, Labette, Linn, Lyon, Marion, Marshall, Montgomery, Morris, Neosho, Reno, Rice, Sumner, Wabaunsee, and Wilson. Hazard mitigation measures statewide will also be eligible for federal funding. Michael L. Karl has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Further damage assessments may lead to additional designations and requests for federal assistance. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-4600.